---
import '../styles/global.css';

const effectiveDate = 'June 8, 2026';
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
		<meta
			name="description"
			content="Privacy policy for PaperBright Text Editor, a browser-based writing app with optional Google Drive live save."
		/>
		<title>Privacy Policy | PaperBright Text Editor</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<main class="mx-auto flex min-h-screen w-full max-w-3xl flex-col gap-4 px-4 py-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
			<header class="theme-panel flex items-center justify-between gap-3 rounded-lg border border-line bg-white/90 px-4 py-3 shadow-sm">
				<a class="flex min-w-0 items-center gap-3 text-inherit no-underline" href="/">
					<div class="paperbright-logo flex h-10 w-10 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-ink text-paper" aria-hidden="true">
						<svg width="25" height="25" viewBox="0 0 25 25" fill="none" role="img">
							<path d="M7 3.5h8.2L20 8.3V21H7V3.5Z" fill="white" />
							<path d="M15.2 3.5V8.3H20" fill="#dbeafe" />
							<path d="M10 12.2h7" stroke="#0a0a0a" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" />
							<path d="M10 15.8h5.2" stroke="#0a0a0a" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" />
							<path d="M7 3.5h8.2L20 8.3V21H7V3.5Z" stroke="white" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linejoin="round" />
							<path d="M6.2 18.8c3.2-1.2 6.8-1.2 10 0" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="1.9" stroke-linecap="round" />
						</svg>
					</div>
					<div>
						<p class="theme-muted text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-muted">PaperBright</p>
						<p class="text-lg font-semibold leading-tight">Privacy Policy</p>
					</div>
				</a>
				<a class="rounded-lg border border-line bg-white px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-inherit no-underline" href="/">Open editor</a>
			</header>

			<article class="theme-panel rounded-lg border border-line bg-white/95 p-5 leading-7 shadow-sm sm:p-7">
				<p class="theme-muted text-sm text-muted">Effective date: {effectiveDate}</p>
				<h1 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold">Privacy Policy</h1>
				<p class="mt-4">
					PaperBright Text Editor is a browser-based writing app. This policy explains what information the app handles when you write,
					save locally, upload custom fonts, or choose to connect Google Drive.
				</p>

				<h2 class="mt-7 text-xl font-semibold">Information PaperBright handles</h2>
				<ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
					<li>Your document text, file name, formatting settings, quick notes, custom font data, and editor preferences may be saved in your browser storage.</li>
					<li>If you upload a custom font, the font file is loaded into your browser and may be stored locally so your draft can reopen with that font.</li>
					<li>If you connect Google Drive, PaperBright receives a temporary Google access token in the browser so it can create or update the text file you save through the app.</li>
				</ul>

				<h2 class="mt-7 text-xl font-semibold">Google Drive access</h2>
				<p class="mt-3">
					PaperBright requests the Google Drive scope <code>https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive.file</code>. This lets the app view
					and manage only Drive files that you create or open with PaperBright. PaperBright does not request full access to your Drive.
				</p>
				<p class="mt-3">
					PaperBright's use and transfer of information received from Google APIs will adhere to the Google API Services User Data
					Policy, including the Limited Use requirements.
				</p>

				<h2 class="mt-7 text-xl font-semibold">How information is used</h2>
				<ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
					<li>To keep your draft available in the same browser.</li>
					<li>To export, import, and format your text.</li>
					<li>To save or update your selected PaperBright text file in Google Drive when Drive live save is enabled.</li>
				</ul>

				<h2 class="mt-7 text-xl font-semibold">What PaperBright does not do</h2>
				<ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
					<li>PaperBright does not sell your document content or Google user data.</li>
					<li>PaperBright does not use Google user data for advertising.</li>
					<li>PaperBright does not run its own user account database for this editor.</li>
				</ul>

				<h2 class="mt-7 text-xl font-semibold">Storage and deletion</h2>
				<p class="mt-3">
					You can delete local PaperBright data by clearing this site's browser storage. You can delete Drive files directly from
					Google Drive. You can also revoke PaperBright's Google access from your Google Account permissions page.
				</p>

				<h2 class="mt-7 text-xl font-semibold">Service providers</h2>
				<p class="mt-3">
					PaperBright is hosted on Vercel, which may process standard hosting logs needed to deliver and protect the website. Google
					processes sign-in and Drive authorization when you choose to connect Google Drive.
				</p>

				<h2 class="mt-7 text-xl font-semibold">Children</h2>
				<p class="mt-3">PaperBright is not directed to children under 13.</p>

				<h2 class="mt-7 text-xl font-semibold">Changes</h2>
				<p class="mt-3">This policy may be updated as PaperBright changes. The effective date will show when the policy was last updated.</p>

				<h2 class="mt-7 text-xl font-semibold">Contact</h2>
				<p class="mt-3">
					For questions, open an issue at
					<a class="font-medium text-signal underline" href="https://github.com/MindMatrix-07/PaperBright">MindMatrix-07/PaperBright</a>.
				</p>
			</article>
		</main>
	</body>
</html>
